############################################################################### 
# Note
############################################################################### 

  This is my more or less gnome setup, there are no auto install scripts
  for this config

  See below how to restore some gnome settings, key shortcuts, extensions
  settings, note that this method is not perfect and future you should
  be careful when doing this on a fresh system install - especially
  with replacing parts of dconf database

############################################################################### 
# Saving and restoring
############################################################################### 

  This should include keyboard shortcuts, key mappings and
  gnome tweaks settings


        dconf dump /org/gnome/ > ./dconf/gnome-settings.ini


  This should export gnome extensions settings


        dconf dump /org/gnome/shell/extensions/ > ./dconf/extensions.ini


  This is how you could restore the saved dconf settings
  NOTE that this will replace the dconf database contents


        dconf load /org/gnome/ < gnome/dconf/gnome-settings.ini
        dconf load /org/gnome/shell/extensions/ < gnome/dconf/extensions.ini


  This is how you can create list of installed gnome extensions


        gnome-extensions list > ./extensions/extensions-list-manual.txt



